@pabsgill The #BubbleNebula, around 11,000 light years from Earth, can be seen as a tiny pearl-like formation in the middle left. 

The #CaveNebula, which is relatively close at only 2,400 light years from Earth, is located on the upper right area of the photo.

#MilkyWay #space https://t.co/bH9dDtpGOV

@pabsgill The California Nebula, also called NGC 1499, was discovered by EE Barnard in 1884. 

The nebula is located around 1,000 light years from Earth. Because of its low surface brightness, it is one of the most difficult astronomical objects to observe.

